ğŸ”§ File-by-File Analysis
1. app.py - Main Flask Application
Purpose: Core backend application handling AI predictions, web routes, and report generation.

Key Components:

AI Model Loading: Uses ViT (Vision Transformer) for image classification
Image Processing: Handles multiple image uploads and camera captures
Disease Classification: Identifies 3 classes: Healthy, Early Blight, Late Blight
Report Generation: Creates PDF and CSV exports
Web API: RESTful endpoints for frontend communication
Key Functions:

predict_single_image()     # AI prediction for single image
export_report()           # PDF/CSV report generation
predict_batch()           # Handle multiple image analysis
Dependencies:

Flask (web framework)
PyTorch (AI model)
Transformers (ViT model)
ReportLab (PDF generation)
PIL (image processing)
fpdf2 (fallback PDF)
2. templates/index.html - Frontend Interface
Purpose: Modern, responsive web interface with camera functionality.

Key Features:

Drag & Drop Upload: Intuitive file selection
Live Camera Capture: Real-time photo capture with preview
Responsive Design: Works on desktop and mobile
Real-time Results: Dynamic result display with animations
Export Controls: PDF and CSV download buttons
JavaScript Classes:

PotatoDiseaseDetector      # Main application controller
- handleFileSelection()    # Process uploaded files
- openCamera()            # Camera modal and stream
- capturePhoto()          # Capture and process photos
- analyzeImages()         # Send to AI for analysis
- exportResults()         # Download reports
UI Sections:

Upload area with dual options (files/camera)
Loading animation with progress bar
Results grid with disease information
Export controls and new analysis button
3. static/style.css - Styling & Design
Purpose: Modern, professional styling with responsive design.

Design System:

Color Palette: Green theme (agricultural focus)
Typography: Inter font family for readability
Layout: CSS Grid and Flexbox for responsiveness
Components: Cards, buttons, modals, tables
Animations: Smooth transitions and hover effects
Key Sections:

:root                     # CSS variables and color scheme
.upload-area             # Drag & drop styling
.camera-modal            # Camera interface design
.result-card             # Disease result display
.confidence-badge        # Color-coded confidence levels
@media queries           # Mobile responsiveness
Responsive Breakpoints:

Desktop: 1200px+
Tablet: 768px - 1199px
Mobile: < 768px
4. requirements.txt - Dependencies
Purpose: Python package dependencies for the project.

Core Dependencies:

captum                   # AI model interpretability
flask                    # Web framework
torch                    # PyTorch deep learning
torchvision             # Computer vision utilities
transformers            # Hugging Face transformers
fpdf2                   # PDF generation
reportlab               # Advanced PDF creation
pillow                  # Image processing
5. potato_disease_model.pth - AI Model
Purpose: Trained Vision Transformer model for disease classification.

Model Details:

Architecture: ViT-Base-Patch16-224
Classes: 3 (Healthy, Early Blight, Late Blight)
Input Size: 224x224 pixels
Accuracy: High precision disease detection
Training: Fine-tuned on potato leaf dataset
Model Components:

model_state_dict         # Trained weights
class_to_idx            # Class mapping
idx_to_class            # Reverse mapping
6. train.py - Model Training Script
Purpose: Script for training the AI model on potato disease dataset.

Training Process:

Data loading and preprocessing
Model architecture setup
Training loop with validation
Model saving and evaluation
Performance visualization
ğŸ¯ Core Functionality
Disease Detection Pipeline:
Image Input â†’ Upload files or capture with camera
Preprocessing â†’ Resize, normalize, tensor conversion
AI Analysis â†’ ViT model prediction with confidence
Result Processing â†’ Format results with disease info
Report Generation â†’ PDF/CSV export with recommendations
Supported Disease Classes:
Healthy Leaves: No disease detected
Early Blight: Alternaria solani infection
Late Blight: Phytophthora infestans infection
